Homer Police Reports

Posted: February 12, 2014 - 1:56pm

Feb. 3

An officer at 10:45 a.m. attended an interview regarding suspicious circumstances.

A woman at 4:15 p.m. reported a juvenile driving out of compliance with restrictions.

Police at 8:39 p.m. made a traffic stop on a driver on Main Street and contacted a probation officer regarding a subject.

A woman at 9:16 p.m. made a 911 call that her adult son living in another state was missing.

A person at 10:47 p.m. reported an assault at a Sterling Highway address. Police responded and took a man into protective custody.

A caller at 9:58 p.m. reported a man walking in the roadway on the Sterling Highway. Police responded and advised the man not to walk in the road.

Feb. 4

A woman at 7:49 a.m. reported horses in the road on West Hill Road. Police responded and contacted the horses’ owner. The horses were secured.

A woman at 11:40 a.m. reported drug activity in the Homer area.

A caller at 3:21 p.m. reported a man going door-to-door in the Kachemak Way area and introducing himself as a UFO inspector. He was asking questions about orange lights. The caller asked for a welfare check on the man. Police could not find the UFO inspector.

A caller at 6:28 p.m. reported being threatened by a man.

Multiple callers at 7:45 p.m. reported seeing flares over Kachemak Bay. All was OK. The U.S. Coast Guard was performing scheduled maneuvers.

A caller at 8:43 p.m. reported drug activity.

Feb. 5

A caller at 2:01 a.m. reported a driver speeding in the Mulliken Avenue area all night.

A man at 3:50 p.m. reported hearing gunshots in the Scenic View Drive area. Police responded but could not locate the source.

A man at 6:04 p.m. asked for traffic information on bicyclists and crosswalks.

A woman at 9:52 p.m. reported loud noise caused by a helicopter in the Grubstake Avenue area.

Feb. 7

A caller at 9:20 a.m. reported a downed tree blocking the road on Ocean Drive.

A man at 10 a.m. reported a tree on a power line on Lakeshore Drive.

A man at 10:30 a.m. made a 911 call of a downed wire blowing in the wind on Lake Street. Police responded and determined it was a cable line. Police notified the appropriate agency and the line was secured.

A person at 11 a.m. made a 911 call of a tree leaning on power lines on the Sterling Highway near Soundview Avenue.

A person at 11:15 a.m. made a 911 call of a downed tree blocking the road on East End Road.

A caller at 11:46 a.m. reported loose roofing from an apartment complex damaged a car’s windshield.

A caller at noon reported a downed tree blocking both lanes of traffic on East Skyline Drive near Paintbrush Court.

A man at 12:38 p.m. reported a downed tree partially blocking the road on Rochelle Road.

A man at 4:15 p.m. reported an icy road on West Hill Road.

A caller at 5:42 p.m. reported a downed tree in the road on Skyline Drive near Ridgeway Court.

A caller at 6:30 p.m. reported icy road conditions on Heath Street.

A man at 6:35 p.m. reported snow drifts in the road near Mile 170 Sterling Highway.

A woman at 6:42 p.m. reported receiving unwanted phone calls and texts from a man.

A caller at 7:03 p.m. reported a hit-and-run crash on Pioneer Avenue.

Feb. 8

A man at 10:43 a.m. made a 911 call of a theft from a car.

A woman at 11:30 a.m. reported being concerned about a unicycle rider in the roadway on Pioneer Avenue.

A woman at 2:20 p.m. reported finding suspicious video material.

A caller at 3:19 p.m. reported a car crash on Pioneer Avenue. Police responded and issued a summons to a 57-year-old man for not having car insurance.

A woman at 3:47 p.m. reported two men carried weapons on Bartlett Street. Police responded.

A man at 5:51 p.m. made a “report every dangerous driver immediately” complaint of a driver on Lake Street. Police stopped the suspect driver, a 51-year-old woman, and issued her a summons for driving while license revoked. They also arrested a 50-year-old woman on a warrant.

A man a 6:36 p.m. made a 911 call that he felt distressed. Police responded and determined the man was OK.

A woman at 7:13 p.m. reported losing her purse at a Sterling Highway address.

A woman at 8:34 p.m. reported a damaged window at a Heath Street address.

Police at 9:56 p.m. stopped a 30-year-old man driving on Pioneer Avenue and issued him a summons for DWLR.

Feb. 9

Police at 12:04 a.m. stopped a driver on East End Road and issued a DUI warning.

A person at 1:18 a.m. made a 911 call reporting an assault at a Pioneer Avenue address. Police responded and issued a “be on the lookout” for a suspect.

Police at 2:24 a.m. provided transportation for two men.

Police at 2:54 a.m. contacted a 49-year-old man on East End Road and arrested him on a federal fugitive-from-justice warrant.

A caller at 3:38 a.m. reported a drunk pedestrian on Pioneer Avenue. Police contacted the person and provided transportation.

A caller at 9 a.m. reported a customer found belongings and a purse outside a Sterling Highway business. Police retrieved the property and contacted the owner.

A man at 4:43 p.m. reported an assault at a Jenny Way address. Police responded and separated the parties for the evening.

Feb. 10

A caller at 2:47 a.m. made a REDDI complaint of a driver on East End Road. Police contacted the suspect driver and helped the driver get home safely. Police warned the person not to drive while on medications.

A caller at 5:50 a.m. reported a medically unstable person driving near Mile 169.5 Sterling Highway. Police stopped the driver and released the person to a relative.

Schley County, GA | Crime Rates

Schley is a county located in GA, and has a population of 3,240. This region is policed by SCHLEY COUNTY.

Schley County has an overall crime rate of 1,574 per 100,000 residents. This is one of the safest regions in the United States. This means that your chances of becoming a victim of any type of crime in Schley County is 1 in 64 if you reside there for a year.

The average overall crime rate for Schley County for the previous 2 years was 799 per 100,000 residents. This means that the crime rate for Schley County has been increasing over time.

Was involved in the transfer of U.S.-origin ship engines, marine generators, and marine power propulsion equipment to Iran for use by the Iranian military, in violation of U.S. export controls.

Added on July 18, 2017 to the Specially Designated Nationals (SDN) list maintained by the U.S. Department of the Treasury's Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC), freezing his assets under U.S. jurisdiction and prohibiting transactions with U.S. parties, pursuant to Executive Order 13382 which targets proliferators of weapons of mass destruction (WMD) and their delivery systems; foreign parties facilitating transactions for the individual or otherwise assisting the individual are subject to U.S. sanctions; added on January 10, 2017 to the U.S. Entity List of end users subject to heightened export license requirements due to involvement in proliferation activities or other activities of national security concern.

Indicted on June 27, 2017, along with the Ramor Group (RG) and Fulya Kalafatoglu Oguzturk, for conspiracy to violate the International Emergency Economic Powers Act (IEEPA) and the Iranian Transactions and Sanctions Regulations (ITSR), and conspiracy to commit money laundering; as president of Ramor Group, from 2013 to 2015 allegedly procured U.S.-origin items without a required license for Qeshm Madkandaloo Shipbuilding Cooperative Co. in Iran, including two 557 horsepower outboard engines, one marine diesel generator, and two Arneson ASD-14 Surface Drives for marine propulsion; the generator and surface devices were allegedly destined for use on the RMS-16, a "high speed composite boat" equipped with a Nasr-type missile system; Qeshm Madkandaloo has provided support to the Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps Navy (IRGC-Navy).

President and sole owner of the Ramor Group; reportedly also a company official at Gatar Madencilik Sanayi ve Ticaret Limited Sirketi, Grt Gemi Sanayi Insaat ve Ticaret Limited Sirketi, and Asha Grup Insaat Madencilik Petrol Gida Tekstil Sanayi ve Ticaret Limited Sirketi; has served as Turkey-based representative of Sina Group, an Iraqi trading and construction company; has acted as Turkey-based representative of Erbil Fruit and Vegetables Distribution Center (FDC), which is based in Iraq.

Arrested in Romania in June 2017, at the request of the United States, in connection with the violations.
